   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Before operating the metering conveyor scale, verify that all safety mechanisms,
               such as the protective housings and covers, are installed and functioning
               properly.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <note>
               <table>
                  <tgroup cols="2">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry/>
                           <entry>
                              <p>Electric Shock</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </note>
            <p>The lockable main switch on the door of the metering conveyor scale control cabinet
               is used to switch off the power supply to the metering conveyor scale. </p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>The cabinet is located on the Hydra-Mix floor (two floors up from the melter
                     control room).</li>
                  <li>When the switch is switched to “Off”, the metering conveyor scale will not
                     work and no movements will occur.   </li>
               </ul>
               <note type="caution">
                  <p>Even after a main switch has been switched off, the following circuits remain
                     live (if present) for the corresponding control cabinet: Lighting for control
                     cabinet, control cabinet socket, control cabinet ventilation.</p>
               </note>
               <p>
                  <fig>
                     <image href="media/image2.jpg" placement="break" align="center"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <note>
               <table>
                  <tgroup cols="2">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry/>
                           <entry>
                              <p>Electric Shock</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </note>
            <p>The E-Stop switch is located at the control cabinet. It shuts down all functions
               and movements. </p>
            <p>
               <p>
                  <note type="caution">
                     <p> E-Stop switches do not disconnect the metering conveyor scale from the
                        power supply. All machine parts that are live during normal operation
                        continue to be live after an emergency stop has been triggered. </p>
                  </note>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <fig>
                     <image href="media/image3.jpg" placement="break" align="center"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <note id="note_myy_qqd_5cc">
               <table id="table_xdk_rqd_5cc">
                  <tgroup cols="2">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry/>
                           <entry>
                              <p>LO/TO (Lockout-Tagout)</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </note>
            <p>The metering conveyor scale also has a service switch to switch off the device. </p>
            <p>
               <ul id="ul_qty_sqd_5cc">
                  <li>The service switch does not completely cut off the metering conveyor scale
                     from the power supply. Lines that are still live even when the service switch
                     is off are identified in orange.</li>
                  <li>LO/TO the service switch before performing maintenance work. </li>
               </ul>
               <p>
                  <fig id="fig_sty_sqd_5cc">
                     <image href="media/image4.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_tty_sqd_5cc"
                            align="center"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>The metering conveyor scale has warning signs for:</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>Dangerous electrical voltage</li>
                  <li>Danger of pulling-in and crushing </li>
               </ul>
               <p>
                  <fig id="fig_ip1_vqd_5cc">
                     <image href="media/image5.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_jp1_vqd_5cc"
                            align="center"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Hazardous materials and substances are transported on the metering conveyor scale.</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>Observe all plant requirements when operating the device.</li>
                  <li>Replace contaminated clothing with clean clothing immediately.</li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ol>
